The article argues that President Trump's immigration deal is a good one and that both parties in Congress should accept it. It states that America's immigration policy has been generous but that free people have the right to determine who can enter their country based on their own interests. The article also mentions that a majority of Americans favor the basic immigration proposals laid out by President Trump, which include a path to citizenship for Dreamers, funding for border security, and reforming lawful pathways for immigrants. The article concludes by emphasizing the need for a democratic process in making immigration policy.